This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it proposes a defense mechanism against membership inference attacks, which is a privacy and security threat. Additionally, the paper also discusses the limitations of existing defenses that leverage differential privacy, which is a common technique used in cryptography and security. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically binary classification and adversarial examples, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, since the primary focus of the paper is on privacy and security, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category.
